). [1] GSTs constitute a superfamily of enzymes with diversified functions . [2] These enzymes are known to decrease the pharmacologic activity of a wide range of structurally unrelated drugs through their conjugation with glutathione (GSH). [3] Furthermore, the GS-conjugated compounds may be actively extruded from the cell through specialized pumps; principally, the multidrug resistance proteins MRP-1 and MRP-2 (ABCC1, ABCC2; ref. 

). [1] In humans, several GST isoforms are differentially expressed and are subdivided into different classes . [2] The Pi class GSTP1-1 is overexpressed in a variety of different human malignancies including lung , colon , stomach , kidney , ovary , mouth , and testis  cancers.
